Political Parties, Government and Organizations in DPRK Call for Promoting Cause of Reunification 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 18 (KCNA) -- Political parties, government and organizations of the DPRK issued a joint statement Wednesday representing the mission of the nation to make this significant year a year of turning point in history by giving a new momentum to the cause of national reunification and the will of all the Koreans to achieve it.
 The Korean nation's movement for reunification has entered into a new historic phase, the statement said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK's access to nukes is a great national event to be especially recorded in the national history spanning 5,000 years. This provided the Korean nation with a sure guarantee for reliably defending its dignity and sovereignty and the peace and security of the country and steadily glorifying the June 15 era of independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Newspapers Rodong Sinmun, Joson Inmingun and Chongnyon Jonwi in a joint editorial for this year took a patriotic initiative to add brilliance to the June 15 reunification era by attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The north and the south of Korea should firmly adhere to the stand of giving importance to the nation, regard it as the best one, put the nation's dignity and interest above anything else, subordinate everything to them and maintain its independent stand, believing in its own strength, not other's. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The political parties and organizations in south Korea should reject cooperation with outsiders doing harm to the fellow countrymen and positively opt for national cooperation from a pro-reunification and patriotic stand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Koreans in the north and the south and overseas should resolutely stand up against the U.S. nuclear racket and war moves against the DPRK, properly distinguishing the aggressive nature of the U.S. nukes and the peace-loving and nation-saving nature and mission of the DPRK's nukes and wage a more dynamic struggle to force the U.S. to pull back its troops, a source of war, from south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities should stop at once their arms buildup and joint military exercises targeted against compatriots. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "presidential elections" to be held in south Korea this year will be a scene of a fierce showdown to choose between peace and war and between reunification and continued division. All the patriotic south Koreans are called upon to form a great alliance against conservatism in order to decisively frustrate the plot of the conservative forces to return to power as it is aimed to spoil the gains made through the publication of the June 15 joint declaration and bring a war holocaust to this land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We ardently call on all the Koreans in the north and the south and overseas to turn out as one in the drive to make this year as a year of attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Koreans should broaden the ways of inter-Korean visits and meetings for reunification paved by the June 15 joint declaration and reenergize cooperation undertakings common to the nation including the tour of Mt. Kumgang and the construction of the Kaesong Industrial Zone. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is necessary to reinforce the June 15 All-Korean Committee and achieve the solidarity and alliance among all the Koreans in order to strengthen the driving force of national reunification movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All political organizations, social organizations and the Koreans at home and abroad aspiring after peace and reunification of the country should actively support and uphold the great Songun policy, the lifeline of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should drop its anachronistic hostile policy toward the DPRK, halt its reckless nuclear row against the DPRK, give up its plot to stifle the latter through sanctions and stop unreasonably interfering in the issues of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is our expectation and belief that the authorities, political parties and organizations of south Korea and all the Koreans at home and abroad would positively turn out in the nation-wide grand march for independent reunification and governments, political parties and organizations of all countries, international organizations, progressives in the world who value justice and truth would extend full support and solidarity to the Korean nation in its cause of independent and peaceful reunification.

Korean People's Greatest Holidays to Be Commemorated in Benin 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 18 (KCNA) -- The Benin Preparatory Committee for Commemorating the Day of the Sun and February 16 was inaugurated with due ceremony in Porto Novo on Jan. 5.
 Present at the inaugural ceremony were members of the Benin-Korea Amicable Association "Long Live Kim Jong Il, Supreme Leader" and the Benin National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea and of General Kim Jong Il's Works and public figures. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hessou Kohovi, chairman of the above-said amicable association and the national committee, was elected chairman of the preparatory committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The preparatory committee decided to hold multifarious functions including seminar, remembrance meeting and photo and book exhibition from January 10 to April 20.

DPRK's Joint New Year Editorial Supported in Mexico 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 18 (KCNA) -- Mexican political parties and organizations including the Socialist Party, the People's Socialist Party, the Fellowship Institute to Honor the Memory of President Kim Il Sung and the Institute for the Study of the Juche Idea made public a joint statement on Jan. 11 in support of the joint New Year editorial of the newspapers of the party, the army and the youth league in the DPRK.
 The joint New Year editorial serves as a great milestone for the Korean people advancing toward brilliant future, the statement said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We fully support the Korean people's struggle to defend the country's sovereignty and the national dignity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Considering that the three principles for national reunification of independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity put forward by President Kim Il Sung are the invariable guideline for achieving Korea's reunification, we support the Korean people in their efforts to reunify the country under the slogan "Add brilliance to the June 15 reunification era by attaching importance to the nation, maintaining peace and achieving unity!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We call upon all the governments and organizations of the world to support Korea's reunification by means of federal formula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United States should drop its hostile policy towards the DPRK and stop threatening it.

Posters Inciting Implementation of Joint New Year Editorial Issued 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 18 (KCNA) -- The Workers' Party of Korea Publishing House, the Mansudae Art Studio, the Central Fine Arts Studio and Pyongyang University of Fine Arts have issued a lot of posters depicting the idea and spirit of the joint New Year editorial.
 Posters including "All for the implementation of the joint New Year editorial!", "Beat louder the drum of Songun revolution!" and "Usher in the heyday of Songun Korea!" call for effecting gigantic changes in the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation, united around leader Kim Jong Il with a single mind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The posters "All-out offensive in building an economic power!" and "Toward the high peak of great prosperous powerful socialist nation!" well depict the firm confidence and will and militant spirit of the Korean people to open a period of all-round efflorescence in the country's prosperity under the banner of Songun revolution this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the posters are "Greater amount of consumer goods!" and "Tap reserves for economizing electric power!" which wittily represent the tasks and ways for improving the people's living standard at present with concise art of drawing and simple themes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And there are also posters of diverse themes conducive to powerfully rousing the WPK members and other working people in the fulfillment of the militant tasks set forth in the joint New Year editorial.

Suppression of Pro-Reunification Patriotic Forces in S. Korea Lambasted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 18 (KCNA) -- The suppression of pro-reunification patriotic forces intensified by the south Korean security authorities from the outset of the new year is nothing but an anti-reunification action aimed to chill the south Korean society's desire to achieve reunification through an alliance with the north and block the national reconciliation and unity.
 Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This repressive campaign betrays the sinister aims of the Grand National Party (GNP) and other ultra-right conservatives of south Korea to create impression that its "security is threatened by the north" by linking those forces standing for progressive reforms with the DPRK in a bid to eliminate those forces supporting the June 15 joint declaration and secure a situation favorable for their contests in the "presidential elections".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such anti-DPRK fascist plot as "spy case" is no longer workable as it is nothing but the outdated last-ditch method employed by those reactionary and wicked force. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The GNP and its followers are working hard to block the progressive development of the south Korean society and come to power by resorting to such hackneyed method. This folly will only invite self-destruction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean security authorities should stop the suppression of the progressive forces and immediately abolish the "National Security Law", a leftover of the era of confrontation, facing up to the trend of the times.

Total Renegotiation on Projected Expansion of U.S. Military Base Demanded in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 18 (KCNA) -- The All-People Measure Committee for Checking the Expansion of the U.S. Military Base in Phyongthaek in south Korea reportedly held a press conference in front of the "defense ministry" on Jan. 12 and demanded a total renegotiation on the plan for the expansion of the U.S. military base.
 The press release read out at the press conference bitterly denounced the act of the "government" to pour blood taxes collected from the people into the building of the U.S. war base. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the burden imposed upon the south Korean "government" for the expansion of the base goes far beyond 10 trillion won, the press release demanded the "government" put a prompt end to such hasty and humiliating undertaking for the expansion of the U.S. military base. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hidden in the reckless remarks of the U.S. forces commander in south Korea resorting to open threat with regard to the expansion of the base is the dastardly aim of shifting onto south Korea the maximum share of the burden for the expansion of the base, stated the press release. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It declared that the committee would vigorously wage the struggle to push the demand for a total renegotiation of the plan for the expansion of the base.

Great Vitality of Music-based Politics
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 18 (KCNA) -- The music-based politics of the Workers' Party of Korea has brought about a great turn in the development of the Korean revolution and its validity and indestructible vitality is being displayed to the fuller as the days go by.
 Kim Jong Il, who set forth a unique idea that a genuine music should meet the demand of the times and contribute to the mission of the times in the early period of his revolutionary activities, has wisely led the work of creating famous art pieces representing the times at each stage of the revolutionary development. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are many famous songs including "Blue Sky over My Country," "We Will Advance with Confidence," "The Road of Victory" and "All Servicepersons and People Will Become Human Bullets and Bombs." For their high ideological and artistic value, they infuse confidence and optimism into the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The contest of artistic groups of KPA officers�f wives which shows a new chapter of the revolutionary soldiers' culture and the national singing contest of working people are held annually amid his concern, giving a revolutionary stamina and enthusiasm to the servicepersons and working people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The vitality of the music-based politics is being manifested more clearly in the Songun era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people, loudly singing songs, have won victory after victory in the fierce showdown with the U.S. imperialists without gun-firing and opened up a broad vista for building a great, prosperous and powerful nation, successfully undergoing the "Arduous March" and the forced march. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Merited State Chorus of the Korean People's Army vigorously aroused the army and people to the struggle for defending socialism in the 1990s when grave situation was created in the country owing to the moves of the imperialists to stifle the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Startling miracles and labor feats are being made in many units from the beginning of the year. These are unthinkable apart from brisk mass cultural and artistic activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The working people of Korea are registering signal successes in all working sites of the socialist construction such as the agricultural and power, coal-mining, metal industry and rail transport sectors, singing louder the songs of struggle and advance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The music-based politics is certain to bring earlier the building of a great, prosperous powerful nation.

Songun, Life and Soul of Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 18 (KCNA) -- "Songun is the life and soul of the country and people and the dignity of the nation," says the joint New Year editorial. This reflects the truth the Korean people had keenly experienced in the course of the revolutionary struggle of Korea, which started and advanced under the banner of Songun.
 President Kim Il Sung, who laid down the slogan "Weapons are our life and soul! Oppose armed force with armed force!" in his early days and pioneered Songun, founded the revolutionary armed force, first of its kind in Korea, in April, Juche 21(1932), thus declaring a war against the one million-strong aggression troops of the Japanese imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He created original guerrilla tactics to win one brilliant victory after another in the anti-Japanese war to accomplish the historic cause of national liberation in August 1945. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After liberation he put forth the foundation of the revolutionary regular armed forces as one of the main tasks in building a new country and developed the Korean People's Revolutionary Army into a modern regular army in a short span of time. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to the revolutionary armed forces, the servicepersons and people could defend with credit the sovereignty of the country and the dignity of the nation in the Fatherland Liberation War (June 1950-July 1953), which was started by the U.S. imperialists to conquer the DPRK in its cradle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the postwar period the President set forth the slogan "Hold a rifle in one hand and a sickle and hammer in the other!" and simultaneously pushed ahead with the economic construction and defence upbuilding and, at the same time, developed and strengthened the KPA to be invincible one. As a result, he smashed every move of the U.S. imperialists and their followers to invade the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il is brilliantly carrying forward the Songun-based idea and leadership of the President and always leading the Korean revolution along the road of victory under the banner of Songun. The Korean people elected him to be chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK and Supreme Commander of the KPA. It was a special event in the Songun history of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the middle of the 1990s the leader frustrated the unprecedentedly intensified aggressive maneuvers of the imperialists and safeguarded the destiny of the country and people with the might of Songun to usher in a fresh heyday of building a great, prosperous and powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are filled with a firm resolution to remain faithful to the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il.

Rodong Sinmun on Guidelines for Korea's Independent Reunification
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 18 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il Sung advanced the three principles for Korea's reunification--independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity--and this is one of his greatest exploits for national reunification.
 Rodong Sinmun stresses this in a by-lined article today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The three principles agreed upon and solemnly declared by the north and the south of Korea are a great reunification programme common to the nation as they show the basic stand and way for realizing the reunification of Korea most properly by its nation itself to meet its independent demands and interests, the author of the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The principle of independence is the essence of the three principles for Korea's reunification, and it calls for realizing the national reunification in an independent way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 National reunification should be achieved on the basis of the principle of independence without dependence on outsiders or their interference. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korea's reunification should be realized by the efforts of its nation responsible for it in accordance with its independent will and requirement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The principle of peaceful reunification is an important component of the three principles as it calls for realizing the national reunification by peaceful means, not through a war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reunification by armed forces would bring countless casualties and disasters upon the Korean nation in the north and the south. As a homogeneous nation, the Koreans in the north and the south can surmount any difference in views through dialogue and negotiation, reconciliation and cooperation to achieve the national unity and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The principle of great national unity calls upon all the Koreans to unite closely and achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country by the strength of their unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korea's reunification is, in essence, a cause of reuniting the divided nation into one. The unity of the whole nation just means national reunification. All the Koreans at home and abroad should be closely united as one under the banner of great unity disregarding differences in ideology and system to build up the driving forces for reunification. This is the main guarantee for achieving the independent national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The struggle for carrying out the three-point task of attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity set forth in the joint New Year editorial is immediately the just patriotic struggle to realize the three principles of national reunification. All the Koreans from all walks of life at home and abroad should turn out to carry out the three-point task.

Friendly Meeting Held with Staff Members of Indian Embassy
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 18 (KCNA) -- The Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries and the Korea-India Friendship Association co-sponsored a friendly meeting with staff members of the Indian embassy here Thursday on the occasion of the 57th Day of the Republic.
 Present there on invitation were Indian Ambassador to the DPRK N.T. Khankhup and staff members of the embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Jon Yong Jin, vice-chairman of the above-said committee who is vice-chairman of the friendship association, and other members of the association. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in the meeting talked to one another about the need to boost the relations of friendship and cooperation between the two countries and had amusement games, deepening the friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They enjoyed a performance given by the Mansudae Art Troupe at the East Pyongyang Grand Theatre on the occasion of the New Year.

Japanese Authorities' Suppression of Chongryon Denounced in Sweden
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 18 (KCNA) -- The Sweden-Korea Friendship Association strongly demands the Japanese authorities immediately stop the suppression of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon), compensate for the damage done to it and respect and guarantee the democratic national rights of the Koreans in Japan.
 The association made this demand in its letter to the prime minister of Japan on Jan. 12. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the Japanese authorities have gone the lengths of backing the ultra-right forces' terrorism against Koreans in Japan, the letter went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is our view that this behavior runs counter to the international law and the spirit of the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese authorities are now seriously threatening the rights of the Koreans in Japan and their security and inciting extreme hostility towards the Korean people instead of apologizing and compensating for the crimes committed against them in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What merits a more serious attention is that such actions are perpetrated in close collusion with the U.S. imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan had better stop dancing to other's tune and strive for the regional peace for its own sake.

Japanese Reactionaries' Suppression of Chongryon and Koreans in Japan Assailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 18 (KCNA) -- The reactionaries of the land of Japs are much upset and taken aback by the might of the DPRK, which enjoys high prestige and exercises strong influence on the international arena while winning one victory after another with Songun. The frantic campaign launched by them against the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and Koreans against this backdrop is no more than their last-ditch efforts to tarnish the image of the DPRK at any cost. A spokesman for the Central Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League said this in a statement Thursday.
 Hooliganism of Japs that occurred one after another from the outset of the new year can not but be politically-motivated brutal terrorism peculiar to the land of Japs which puts any other terrorist organization into the shade in its objective and methods, the statement said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are getting extremely hostile to Chongryon and Koreans in Japan and persecuting and suppressing them, making it hard for them to live in Japan for the mere reason that they support and follow the DPRK. This clearly proves once again that they are a pack of brutes in human skin and brazen-faced robbers whose means of living is high-handed practices and terrorism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japs hell-bent on unjustifiable terrorism against Chongryon and Koreans in Japan in gross violation of elementary human ethics and the international law are bound to be brought to a tribunal by the conscience of the world people who love truth and peace and face a stern judgment of the times and history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries had better immediately stop the reckless moves against Chongryon and Koreans as they are little short of digging their own graves.
